Mr Flemming, a music instructor, has run nine 5K races and four 10Ks.

'Hopefully, next time this year I'll be running the full marathon,' he told Detroit Free Press.

Before he began his weight loss journey, Mr Flemming was pre-diabetic and had been struggling with depression and alcoholism, drinking a fifth of vodka mixed with a liter of soda each night.

'My typical fast-food meal was a double cheeseburger with a large pop and large fries,' Flemming wrote on his blog.

