To manage her condition, Eastham follows an extremely healthy lifestyle, and never takes her well-being for granted.

A friendship grew, and Mr Flemming began to confide in her about his weight problems, and about his drinking, a secret he'd kept even from his parents.

He was expecting sympathy, but was thrown by her response.

